{
  "chapterIndex": 3,
  "pageIndex": 10,
  "blocks": [
    {
      "type": "narration",
      "content": "The gallery was quieter than either of them expected."
    },
    {
      "type": "narration",
      "content": "The kind of quiet that didn’t demand silence—but encouraged it."
    },
    {
      "type": "narration",
      "content": "Cassandra slowed when they stepped inside."
    },
    {
      "type": "narration",
      "content": "Ethan stopped completely."
    },
    {
      "type": "narration",
      "content": "It was subtle, but she noticed."
    },
    {
      "type": "dialogue",
      "character": "Cassandra",
      "content": "You do that."
    },
    {
      "type": "dialogue",
      "character": "Ethan",
      "content": "Do what?"
    },
    {
      "type": "dialogue",
      "character": "Cassandra",
      "content": "Pause like this."
    },
    {
      "type": "dialogue",
      "character": "Ethan",
      "content": "Like what?"
    },
    {
      "type": "dialogue",
      "character": "Cassandra",
      "content": "Like you don’t want to miss something."
    },
    {
      "type": "narration",
      "content": "Ethan looked back at the paintings."
    },
    {
      "type": "dialogue",
      "character": "Ethan",
      "content": "I usually do."
    },
    {
      "type": "dialogue",
      "character": "Cassandra",
      "content": "Miss things?"
    },
    {
      "type": "narration",
      "content": "He nodded slightly."
    },
    {
      "type": "dialogue",
      "character": "Ethan",
      "content": "People. Moments. Timing."
    },
    {
      "type": "narration",
      "content": "Cassandra studied him for a second."
    },
    {
      "type": "dialogue",
      "character": "Cassandra",
      "content": "You don’t seem like someone who misses much."
    },
    {
      "type": "dialogue",
      "character": "Ethan",
      "content": "That’s because I notice after."
    },
    {
      "type": "narration",
      "content": "That landed somewhere deeper than either of them expected."
    },
    {
      "type": "narration",
      "content": "They moved through the space slowly."
    },
    {
      "type": "narration",
      "content": "No rush."
    },
    {
      "type": "narration",
      "content": "No pressure to talk."
    },
    {
      "type": "narration",
      "content": "Just the soft rhythm of footsteps and the quiet presence of things made by people who didn’t want to forget something."
    },
    {
      "type": "narration",
      "content": "Cassandra stopped in front of one painting."
    },
    {
      "type": "narration",
      "content": "Muted colors."
    },
    {
      "type": "narration",
      "content": "Soft edges."
    },
    {
      "type": "narration",
      "content": "Something abstract—but not empty."
    },
    {
      "type": "dialogue",
      "character": "Cassandra",
      "content": "What do you see?"
    },
    {
      "type": "narration",
      "content": "Ethan stepped beside her."
    },
    {
      "type": "narration",
      "content": "Close enough that their shoulders almost touched."
    },
    {
      "type": "narration",
      "content": "He leaned slightly, studying it."
    },
    {
      "type": "dialogue",
      "character": "Ethan",
      "content": "It feels like…"
    },
    {
      "type": "narration",
      "content": "he started, then stopped."
    },
    {
      "type": "dialogue",
      "character": "Cassandra",
      "content": "Like what?"
    },
    {
      "type": "narration",
      "content": "He exhaled."
    },
    {
      "type": "dialogue",
      "character": "Ethan",
      "content": "Like someone trying to hold onto something that’s already fading."
    },
    {
      "type": "narration",
      "content": "Cassandra didn’t respond right away."
    },
    {
      "type": "narration",
      "content": "Because that—"
    },
    {
      "type": "narration",
      "content": "felt too accurate."
    },
    {
      "type": "narration",
      "content": "She looked at him instead."
    },
    {
      "type": "narration",
      "content": "Not the painting."
    },
    {
      "type": "narration",
      "content": "Him."
    },
    {
      "type": "dialogue",
      "character": "Cassandra",
      "content": "You’re really good at that."
    },
    {
      "type": "dialogue",
      "character": "Ethan",
      "content": "At what?"
    },
    {
      "type": "dialogue",
      "character": "Cassandra",
      "content": "Seeing things people don’t say out loud."
    },
    {
      "type": "narration",
      "content": "Ethan glanced at her."
    },
    {
      "type": "narration",
      "content": "Their shoulders touched this time."
    },
    {
      "type": "narration",
      "content": "Neither of them moved."
    }
  ]
}